This paper involves the use of deep reinforcement learning for MDP planning, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of transfer learning, which is relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper focuses on domain-independent probabilistic planners, which is related to programming languages (cs.PL).
